=head1 DESCRIPTION

A gateway is an Backup Gateway appliance that runs on the customer's
network to provide seamless connectivity to backup storage in the
Amazon Web Services Cloud.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 GatewayArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the gateway. Use the C<ListGateways>
operation to return a list of gateways for your account and Amazon Web
Services Region.


=head2 GatewayDisplayName => Str

The display name of the gateway.


=head2 GatewayType => Str

The type of the gateway.


=head2 HypervisorId => Str

The hypervisor ID of the gateway.


=head2 LastSeenTime => Str

The last time Backup gateway communicated with the gateway, in Unix
format and UTC time.



